This paper deals with the application of reinforcement learning and deep learning techniques for computation offloading in IoT devices with energy harvesting. The paper focuses on wireless networks with multiple MEC devices, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The use of reinforcement learning and deep learning techniques for computation offloading falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also deals with information theory aspects such as radio bandwidth and energy harvesting, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper deals with the optimization of energy consumption and computation delay, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
